File: Sub-contracted cleaning workers at Eskom have spent another day protesting outside the Duvha power station near Witbank in Mpumalanga. Pixabay/Cocoparisienne JOHANNESBURG - Eskom will be implementing load reduction in areas of the Free State, Mpumalanga, Limpopo and KwaZulu-Natal. The load reduction will take place between 5pm and 10pm on Saturday. READ: Eskom suspends load-shedding In Limpopo, residents in Mopani, Waterberg, and Sekhukhune Districts will be affected. In the Free State, Thabo Mofutsanyana District will be experiencing load reduction. KwaZulu-Natal and Mpumalanga will also be experiencing power cuts. Eskom Load Reduction Notice
